{
  "analysis": "I'm starting with a clean environment as root. I need to set up: 1) A bare git repository at `/git/server`, 2) An SSH server for git clone/push access, 3) A post-receive hook to deploy pushed content to a web root, 4) A web server on port 8080 to serve the files.",
  "plan": "First,

 check what's installed, then install git, openssh-server, and a lightweight web server (nginx or python3). Create the bare repo, configure the post-receive hook, set up SSH, and start the web server.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "which git nginx sshd python3\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /etc/os-release | head -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}

